Features for 0.1:

  --> Upon completion of v0.1, VZTools should provide most necessary
      information and most critical actions via the lower-level
      interface.

  Adapters
    - veinfo [DONE - 11/12]
    - vestat [DONE - 11/13]
    - vzcalc [DONE - 11/14]
    - vzcpucheck [DONE - 11/14]
    - vzlist [DONE - 11/13]
    - vzmemcheck
    - vzctl
      - start
      - stop
      - create
      - destroy
      - network settings
      - qos settings

Features for 0.2:
  
  Adapters
    - vzctl
      - exec
      - top (via exec)

  API
    - Node
      - listing VEs
      - Node-wide stats
    - VE
      - stats
      - creating and destroying
      - starting and stopping
      - network setting and status
      - qos settings and status
 
  Tools
    - ovzstat
        --> a basic vzstat replacement, primary as a proof of concept.


Features for 0.3:

  Adapters
    - vzpkgadd
    - vzpkgcache
    - vzpkgls
    - vzpkgrm

  API
    - VE
      - exec
      - top

  Tools
    - ovzadm
        --> an interactive shell of sorts, like web console
            for command-line.